latestPosts.caption:
13 kgs weight loss journey. 3 more to go.

Disclaimer first - I am only sharing what worked for me and sharing my experience.

I had undergone cesarean delivery in jan 2023 and before that in Apr 2015. 

1. Start early - I started 15 mins walk in hospital itself. And once I reach home I made sure that I am walking in home whenever I can.
2. Focus on healthy eating - I only had moong dal, roti, khichdi , sooji kheer religiously for 40 days. Since I was also eating Panjiri so I started tea/milk without sugar. 
3. If you are breast feeding then you would loose weight eventually not immediately. So this may cause a worry at that time but is really helpful.
4. Drink water alternative  like buttermilk, nariyal pani. Buttermilk helps in skin cleansing and also in milk production. I have not taken ajwain water my doc told me that if you would take ajwain water then you have to increase water intake as well. Avoid taking cold water and take lukewarm water wherever you can like early morning , after walk.
5. I take one mug of green tea everyday, it helps me in relaxing and in reliving constipation.
6. Ghee works wonder for your skin you have to balance it out in moderate quantity.
7. Go for walk - once your doctor gives you a go ahead and if you feel comfortable then start with some light exercise , I started walk after 30 days 
8. You would feel hungry at odd times so always have something healthy snack near your bedside table , I used to munch on bhune kale chane.

I started late after my first delivery and it became very difficult to loose that extra fat. I had to do intermittent fasting like I never used to take dinner. So this time my suggestion would be start as soon as you can.

In short 
1. check what you are eating , you have to eat healthy. Diet control is must
2. Increase water intake
3. Do 30 mins exercise daily
